{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 16:11:28.989201", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary of Network Health\n- Control plane (EBGP across the Clos fabric) is healthy. All BGP sessions on leaves, spines, and super-spine are Established with consistent prefix counts.\n- Data plane is healthy for the rest of the fabric; multiple hosts show successful reachability between subnets.\n- A localized endpoint connectivity failure exists for pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2).\n\nDetected Anomalies\n- End-to-end reachability to/from pc_0_1 fails:\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: 100% loss; “Destination Host Unreachable” generated by 172.16.0.43 (leaf_router_0_1).\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: “Network is unreachable” (no route / interface down on pc_0_1).\n- ARP resolution to 10.0.1.2 from the leaf fails:\n  - leaf_router_0_1: ip neigh on host-facing interface shows “10.0.1.2 FAILED”.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 cannot ping 10.0.1.2.\n\nLocalization of Fault\n- Fault domain: Access segment for subnet 10.0.1.0/24 between leaf_router_0_1 (10.0.1.1) and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2).\n- Leaf side:\n  - Interface eth4 (10.0.1.1/24) is UP; kernel route for 10.0.1.0/24 present; BGP adjacencies to spines are up.\n  - ethtool on leaf eth4 reports “Link detected: yes”.\n- Host side (pc_0_1):\n  - Interface eth0 is DOWN (ip addr shows state DOWN).\n  - No routing table entries (ip route empty), consistent with interface down.\n  - ethtool on pc_0_1 eth0 reports “Link detected: no”.\n\nRoot Cause\n- The endpoint pc_0_1 has its NIC (eth0) down (no carrier/link), causing:\n  - No ARP responses on 10.0.1.0/24.\n  - Upstream ICMP “Destination Host Unreachable” from the leaf when other hosts try to reach 10.0.1.2.\n  - pc_0_1’s inability to send traffic (“Network is unreachable”) due to interface down and missing default route.\n\nCorroborating Evidence\n- Reachability matrix: all tested cross-subnet paths succeed except those involving pc_0_1.\n- leaf_router_0_1 routing table includes 10.0.1.0/24 connected via eth4 and all other 10.x/24 networks learned over BGP; indicates the fabric control plane is intact.\n- BGP Summaries:\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 4 neighbors up; receiving 7 prefixes from each spine neighbor.\n  - spines and super-spine: all neighbors Established; expected prefix counts.\n- ICMP error source 172.16.0.43 corresponds to leaf_router_0_1 (eth1), confirming the failure arises at the last hop before the host due to ARP/layer-2 failure toward 10.0.1.2.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- Only pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) is affected; it is unreachable from the rest of the network and cannot reach others.\n- No indications of broader fabric issues; routing and other host connectivity operate nominally.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10140, "output_tokens": 2234, "total_tokens": 12374, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9600}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1472}}}
